The coefficient of variation (CV) can measure the overall fluctuation of the data. According to Nielsen’s method, CV is classified into three categories25: CV < 10% (weak variation), 10% ≤ CV ≤ 100% (moderate variation), and CV > 100% (strong variation). We use the coefficient of variation to analyze the distribution characteristics of SOC content at sampling points in different forest land types from both horizontal and vertical profile perspectives. The calculation formula is:1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
